title: Prince Andrew invited Epstein to palace after conviction
description: Newly released emails have revealed that Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor invited Jeffrey Epstein to Buckingham Palace, two years after the disgraced financier was jailed for a sexual offence involving a minor in the United States. #US #Epstein

title: Terrified bystander captures fatal amusement ride collapse in India
description: A bystander captured the terrifying moment an amusement ride collapsed at a popular fair just south of Delhi, India, on 7th February, killing a police inspector who sustained fatal injuries after the other end of the swing collapsed on him during rescue.    People can be seen trying to help those trapped in the collapsed ride, before the near side of the structure completely gives way, crushing many bystanders.   Two individuals were arrested in connection with the collapse.   #India #ridecrash

title: Second deadly wrong-way crash on Mitchell Freeway | 7NEWS
description: Two people have died in a wrong-way crash on Mitchell Freeway in Butler, marking the second fatal collision on the same stretch of road in four months. A 24-year-old man and a 56-year-old woman were killed after the man drove on the wrong side of the freeway, with investigations revealing both this incident and the previous October fatality involved drivers entering from the same Romeo Road off-ramp. Local residents and authorities are questioning whether confusing signage at the intersection is contributing to these deadly accidents. title: Violent clashes as thousands protest Israeli president's visit | 7NEWS
description: Intense clashes erupted between police and approximately 6,000 Palestine protesters in Sydney's CBD during Israeli President Isaac Herzog's visit to Australia. Police used capsicum spray and physical force to disperse crowds, resulting in 27 arrests and 10 injured officers. Herzog addressed the Jewish community at the TikTok Entertainment Centre and laid a wreath at the Bondi terror attack site that claimed 15 lives, whilst protests also occurred in Melbourne, Brisbane, Cairns, Canberra and Perth. title: Jimmy Lai jailed, ship sinks, Italian heist foiled | 7NEWS
description: Hong Kong pro-democracy tycoon and British citizen Jimmy Lai has been sentenced to 20 years in prison for colluding with foreign forces, with parole eligibility only in his late 90s. A container ship sank off Thailand's coast after dramatically keeling over, requiring rescue operations for the crew and triggering efforts to contain a large oil spill. An armed gang in Italy attempted to rob a cash vehicle on a highway by impersonating police and using explosives, but were thwarted by a defensive foam mechanism inside the vehicle.
